ia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/TerracesBenGurion2.jpg/400px-TerracesBenGurion2.jpg 2x" data-file-width="640" data-file-height="480" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:TerracesBenGurion2.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\nThe <a href="/wiki/Shrine_of_the_B%C3%A1b" title="Shrine of the B\xc3\xa1b">Shrine of the B\xc3\xa1b</a> at the <a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_World_Centre" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad World Centre">Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad World Centre</a>, in Haifa, Israel</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The <b>Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith</b> is an emerging global religion founded by <a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27u%27ll%C3%A1h" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'u\'ll\xc3\xa1h">Bah\xc3\xa1\'u\'ll\xc3\xa1h</a>, a nineteenth-century <a href="/wiki/Iran" title="Iran">Iranian</a> exile. <b>"Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad"</b> is either an adjective referring to this religion, or the term for a follower of Bah\xc3\xa1\'u\'ll\xc3\xa1h.</p>\n<p>Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad theology speaks of <a href="/wiki/Three_Onenesses" class="mw-redirect" title="Three Onenesses">three interlocking unities</a>: the oneness of God (<a href="/wiki/Monotheism" title="Monotheism">monotheism</a>); the oneness of his prophets or messengers; and the oneness of humanity (equality, <a href="/wiki/Democratic_globalization" title="Democratic globalization">globalism</a>). These three principles have a profound impact on the theological and social teachings of this religion.</p>\n<p>Religion is seen as a progressively unfolding process of education, by God, through his messengers, to a constantly evolving human family. <a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27u%27ll%C3%A1h" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'u\'ll\xc3\xa1h">Bah\xc3\xa1\'u\'ll\xc3\xa1h</a> is seen as the most recent, pivotal, but not final of God\'s messengers. He announced that his major purpose is to lay the spiritual foundations for a new global civilization of peace and harmony, which Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xads expect to gradually arise.</p>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"><b><a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith">Learn more about Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith...</a></b></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="portal-column-left-wide">\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid black; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #000066; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith/Featured_article&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_article">Selected article</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid black; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: white;opacity: 1; color: #000000; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div class="floatright"><a href="/wiki/File:Willmette_how.jpg" class="image" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad House of Worship in the United States"><img alt="Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad House of Worship in the United States" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/39/Willmette_how.jpg/220px-Willmette_how.jpg" width="220" height="165" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/39/Willmette_how.jpg/330px-Willmette_how.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/39/Willmette_how.jpg/440px-Willmette_how.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1000" data-file-height="750" /></a></div>\n<p>There are currently seven <b><a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_House_of_Worship" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad House of Worship">Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Houses of Worship</a></b> around the world, although <a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith">Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad</a> communities own many properties where they plan for Houses of Worship to be constructed as the Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad community grows and develops.</p>\n<p>The name used in the Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad writings for Houses of Worship is Ma<u>sh</u>riqu\'l-A<u>dh</u>k\xc3\xa1r (Dawning-place of the Remembrance of God). All Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad temples share certain <a href="/wiki/Architecture" title="Architecture">architectural</a> elements, only two of which are specified by Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad scripture, that they are nine-sided and surmounted by <a href="/wiki/Dome" title="Dome">domes</a>.</p>\n<p>Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Houses of Worship are open to people of all faiths - or of no particular faith. Services focus solely on the worship of <a href="/wiki/God" title="God">God</a>. There are no collections and no sermons. Only the Word of God is uttered within the Temple, with readings from all the Holy Writings of the earth. The only <a href="/wiki/Musical_instrument" title="Musical instrument">instrument</a> used is the human voice, and the <a href="/wiki/Choir" title="Choir">choir</a> in any Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad House of Worship sings without instrumental accompaniment. No sermons or lectures are permitted inside the House of Worship. As the <a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith">Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith</a> has no <a href="/wiki/Priesthood" class="mw-redirect" title="Priesthood">priesthood</a>, ordinary members of the community - men and women, adults and children - read the texts.</p>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"><b><a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_House_of_Worship" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad House of Worship">Read more...</a></b></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid black; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #000066; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith/Did_you_know&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Did_you_know.3F">Did you know?</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid black; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: white;opacity: 1; color: #000000; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<p>..that the <b><a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith">Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith</a></b> speaks of three core assertions, sometimes termed the "three onenesses": the <a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_concept_of_God" class="mw-redirect" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad concept of God">unity of God</a>, the <a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith_and_the_unity_of_religion" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith and the unity of religion">unity of religion</a>, and the <a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith_and_the_unity_of_humanity" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith and the unity of humanity">unity of mankind</a>?</p>\n<p>In addition to these three onenesses the following principles are frequently listed as a quick summary of the Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad teachings.</p>\n<dl>\n<dd>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Progressive_revelation_(Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD)" title="Progressive revelation (Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad)">Progressive revelation</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith_and_Feminism" class="mw-redirect" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith and Feminism">Equality of women and men</a></li>\n<li>Elimination of all forms of prejudice</li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/World_peace" title="World peace">World peace</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith_and_science" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith and science">Harmony of religion and science</a></li>\n<li>Independent investigation of truth</li>\n<li>The need for <a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith_and_education" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith and education">universal compulsory education</a></li>\n<li>The need for a <a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith_and_auxiliary_language" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith and auxiliary language">universal auxiliary language</a></li>\n<li>Obedience to government and non-involvement in politics</li>\n<li>Elimination of extremes of wealth and poverty</li>\n</ul>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"><b><a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_teachings" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad teachings">Read more...</a></b></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid black; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #000066; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith/Featured_scripture&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_scripture">Selected scripture</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid black; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: white;opacity: 1; color: #000000; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<p>The <i>Kalimat-i-Maknunih</i> or <b>Hidden Words</b> were written by <a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27u%27ll%C3%A1h" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'u\'ll\xc3\xa1h">Bah\xc3\xa1\'u\'ll\xc3\xa1h</a> in the form of a collection of short utterances, 71 in Arabic and 82 in Persian, in which Bah\xc3\xa1\'u\'ll\xc3\xa1h claims to have taken the basic essence of certain spiritual truths and written them in brief form. Here is an excerpt from the book:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd>O SON OF SPIRIT!</dd>\n<dd>My first counsel is this: Possess a pure, kindly and radiant heart, that thine may be a sovereignty ancient, imperishable and everlasting.\n<dl>\n<dd>(Bah\xc3\xa1\'u\'ll\xc3\xa1h, The Arabic Hidden Words)</dd>\n</dl>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n<dl>\n<dd>O SON OF BEING!</dd>\n<dd>Love Me, that I may love thee. If thou lovest Me not, My love can in no wise reach thee. Know this, O servant.\n<dl>\n<dd>(Bah\xc3\xa1\'u\'ll\xc3\xa1h, The Arabic Hidden Words)</dd>\n</dl>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n<dl>\n<dd>O SON OF DUST!</dd>\n<dd>Verily I say unto thee: Of all men the most negligent is he that disputeth idly and seeketh to advance himself over his brother. Say, O brethren! Let deeds, not words, be your adorning.\n<dl>\n<dd>(Bah\xc3\xa1\'u\'ll\xc3\xa1h, The Persian Hidden Words)</dd>\n</dl>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"><b><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://reference.bahai.org/en/t/b/HW/">More Hidden Words</a></b></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid black; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #000066; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith/Featured_picture&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_picture">Selected picture</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid black; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: white;opacity: 1; color: #000000; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div class="thumb tright">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:172px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Bahaistar.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9c/Bahaistar.jpg/170px-Bahaistar.jpg" width="170" height="170" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9c/Bahaistar.jpg/255px-Bahaistar.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9c/Bahaistar.jpg/340px-Bahaistar.jpg 2x" data-file-width="450" data-file-height="450" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Bahaistar.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\nA stylized nine pointed star, with the calligraphy of the Greatest Name in the centre.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The most commonly used Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad symbol is the 9 pointed star. The significance of the number nine comes from several sources. One of the sacred languages of the Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad holy texts is <a href="/wiki/Arabic_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Arabic language">Arabic</a>, whose alphabet can be used to represent numbers, attaching a <a href="/wiki/Abjad_numerals" title="Abjad numerals">numerical value to words</a>. The numerical value of Bah\xc3\xa1\xe2\x80\x99 is 9.</p>\n<p>The Greatest Name, or more fully, the calligraphy of the Greatest Name of God, is another Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad symbol. It is an <a href="/wiki/Arabic_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Arabic language">Arabic</a> calligraphic rendering of "Y\xc3\xa1 Bah\xc3\xa1\'ul \'Abh\xc3\xa1" (\xd9\x8a\xd8\xa7 \xd8\xa8\xd9\x87\xd8\xa7\xd8\xa1 \xd8\xa7\xd9\x84\xd8\xa3\xd8\xa8\xd9\x87\xd9\x89 usually translated as "O Glory of the Most Glorious!"). This rendering was originally drawn by the eminent early <a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith">Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad</a> calligrapher <a href="/wiki/Mishkin_Qalam" class="mw-redirect" title="Mishkin Qalam">Mishkin Qalam</a>, and later adopted by Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xads everywhere.</p>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"><b><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Featured_pictures" title="Wikipedia:Featured pictures">More featured pictures...</a></b></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid black; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #000066; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith/Wikiprojects&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Wikiprojects">Wikiprojects</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid black; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: white;opacity: 1; color: #000000; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Religion" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Religion">Wikipedia:WikiProject Religion</a></li>\n</ul>\n<dl>\n<dd>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith">Wikipedia:WikiProject Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith</a></li>\n</ul>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="portal-column-right-narrow">\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid black; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #000066; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith/Selected_Religious_Figure&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_Religious_Figure">Selected Religious Figure</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid black; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: white;opacity: 1; color: #000000; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<p><b>M\xc3\xadrz\xc3\xa1 Husayn-`Al\xc3\xad</b> (<a href="/wiki/Persian_language" title="Persian language">Persian</a>: <span lang="fa" dir="rtl" xml:lang="fa">\xd9\x85\xdb\x8c\xd8\xb1\xd8\xb2\xd8\xa7 \xd8\xad\xd8\xb3\xdb\x8c\xd9\x86\xd8\xb9\xd9\x84\xdb\x8c</span>\xe2\x80\x8e\xe2\x80\x8e) (b: <a href="/wiki/1817" title="1817">1817</a> - d: <a href="/wiki/1892" title="1892">1892</a>), who later took the title of <a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27u%27ll%C3%A1h" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'u\'ll\xc3\xa1h">Bah\xc3\xa1\'u\'ll\xc3\xa1h</a> (<a href="/wiki/Arabic_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Arabic language">Arabic</a>: <span lang="ar" dir="rtl" xml:lang="ar">\xd8\xa8\xd9\x87\xd8\xa7\xd8\xa1\xd8\xa7\xd9\x84\xd9\x84\xd9\x87</span>\xe2\x80\x8e\xe2\x80\x8e "Glory of God") was the founder-prophet of the <a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith">Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith</a>.</p>\n<p>He claimed to fulfill the <a href="/wiki/B%C3%A1bism" title="B\xc3\xa1bism">B\xc3\xa1b\xc3\xad</a> prophecy of "<a href="/wiki/He_whom_God_shall_make_manifest" title="He whom God shall make manifest">He whom God shall make manifest</a>", but in a broader sense he also claimed to be the "supreme Manifestation of God" referring to the fulfillment of the <a href="/wiki/Eschatology" title="Eschatology">eschatological</a> expectations of a prophetic cycle beginning with <a href="/wiki/Adam_and_Eve" title="Adam and Eve">Adam</a>, and including <a href="/wiki/Abrahamic_religion" class="mw-redirect" title="Abrahamic religion">Abrahamic religions</a>, as well as <a href="/wiki/Zoroastrianism" title="Zoroastrianism">Zoroastrianism</a>, the great <a href="/wiki/Dharmic_religions" class="mw-redirect" title="Dharmic religions">Dharmic religions</a>, and others. Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xads see Bah\xc3\xa1\'u\'ll\xc3\xa1h as the initiator of a new religion, as <a href="/wiki/Jesus" title="Jesus">Jesus</a> or <a href="/wiki/Muhammad" title="Muhammad">Muhammad</a> \xe2\x80\x94 but also the initiator of a new cycle, like that attributed to Adam.</p>\n<p>During his lifetime, Bah\xc3\xa1\'u\'ll\xc3\xa1h left a large volume of writings. The <a href="/wiki/Kit%C3%A1b-i-Aqdas" title="Kit\xc3\xa1b-i-Aqdas">Kit\xc3\xa1b-i-Aqdas</a>, and the <a href="/wiki/Kit%C3%A1b-i-%C3%8Dq%C3%A1n" title="Kit\xc3\xa1b-i-\xc3\x8dq\xc3\xa1n">Book of Certitude</a> are recognized as primary Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad theological works, and the <a href="/wiki/Hidden_Words" title="Hidden Words">Hidden Words</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Seven_Valleys" class="mw-redirect" title="Seven Valleys">Seven Valleys</a> as primary mystical treatises.</p>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"><b><a href="/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27u%27ll%C3%A1h" title="Bah\xc3\xa1\'u\'ll\xc3\xa1h">Read more...</a></b></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid black; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #000066; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith/Things_you_can_do&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Things_you_can_do">Things you can do</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid black; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: white;opacity: 1; color: #000000; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<ul>\n<li>Contribute to related articles.</li>\n<li>Suggest new feature articles and pictures.</li>\n<li>Write new articles like <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Requested_articles/Social_sciences/Religion#Babism_and_Bah.C3.A1.27.C3.AD_Faith" title="Wikipedia:Requested articles/Social sciences/Religion">these</a>.</li>\n<li>Contribute to a wikibook about the <a class="external text" href="http://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith">Baha\'i Faith</a></li>\n<li>Contribute to the <a class="external text" href="http://en.wikiversity.org/wiki/Topic:Baha%27i_Studies">Baha\'i Studies</a> page in wikiversity</li>\n</ul>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid black; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #000066; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith/Categories&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Categories">Categories</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid black; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: white;opacity: 1; color: #000000; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<p>Main Category:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><big><a href="/wiki/Category:Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_Faith" title="Category:Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith"><b>Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith</b></a></big></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Detailed information about the Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad Faith can be found under these sub-categories:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><b><a href="/wiki/Category:Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%ADs" title="Category:Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xads">Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xads</a></b>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Category:Bah%C3%A1%27%C3%AD_central_figures" title="Category:Bah\xc3\xa1\'\xc3\xad central figures">Central Figures</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Category:Family_of_Bah%C3%A1%27u%27ll%C3%A1h" title="Category:Family of Bah\xc3